==English==

===Etymology===
First attested in mid 13th century. From {{inh|en|enm|abrood||broadly widely scattered}}, from {{m|enm|a-||on, in}} + {{m|enm|brood||broad}}. Equivalent to {{prefix|en|a|broad}}.

